        <!--empty paragraphs get left behind.-->
        <para id="id188962">In mathematical form, subtracting <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:mover></m:math> from
<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:mover></m:math> gives a new vector <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>c</m:mi><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:mover></m:math>:</para>
        <equation id="id189012">
          <m:math overflow="scroll" mode="display">
            <m:mtable displaystyle="true">
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd columnalign="right">
                  <m:mover accent="true">
                    <m:mi>c</m:mi>
                    <m:mo>→</m:mo>
                  </m:mover>
                </m:mtd>
                <m:mtd>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                </m:mtd>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mover accent="true">
                      <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>→</m:mo>
                    </m:mover>
                    <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                    <m:mover accent="true">
                      <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>→</m:mo>
                    </m:mover>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
              <m:mtr>
                <m:mtd/>
                <m:mtd>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                </m:mtd>
                <m:mtd columnalign="left">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mover accent="true">
                      <m:mi>b</m:mi>
                      <m:mo>→</m:mo>
                    </m:mover>
                    <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                      <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                      <m:mover accent="true">
                        <m:mi>a</m:mi>
                        <m:mo>→</m:mo>
                      </m:mover>
                      <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mtd>
              </m:mtr>
            </m:mtable>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        <para id="id189102">This clearly shows that subtracting vector <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:mover></m:math> from
<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:mover></m:math> is the same as adding <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mrow><m:mo>(</m:mo><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:mover><m:mo>)</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math> to
<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>b</m:mi><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:mover></m:math>. Look at the following examples of vector
subtraction.</para>
        <para id="id189179">
          <figure id="id189182">
            <media id="id189182_media" alt="">
              <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/PG11C1_037.png" id="id189182_onlineimage" width="154"><!-- NOTE: attribute width changes image size online (pixels). original width is 154. --></image>
              <image mime-type="application/postscript" for="pdf" src="../../media/PG11C1_037.eps" id="id189182_printimage"/>
            </media>
          </figure>
        </para>
        <para id="id189188">
          <figure id="id189192">
            <media id="id189192_media" alt="">
              <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/PG11C1_038.png" id="id189192_onlineimage" width="188"><!-- NOTE: attribute width changes image size online (pixels). original width is 188. --></image>
              <image mime-type="application/postscript" for="pdf" src="../../media/PG11C1_038.eps" id="id189192_printimage"/>
            </media>
